+public class AuthenticatedUser extends AbstractAuthenticatedUser","[{'comment': ""The way this is implemented, here, these attributes (tokens) would not be available to connections stored in the JDBC module, since the module you've extended, here, is the LDAP-specific one.  In order for this to cover multiple authentication modules, you'll either have to implement this at one of the parent classes (`AbstractAuthenticatedUser` perhaps) or across multiple modules.  Of course, that doesn't all have to be done with this one pull request - this can just tackle LDAP for now - but the base changes that go into it probably need to at least make it available for other extensions to implement.

The other advantage of at least creating the abstract methods within one of the parent classes is avoiding having to do the type-casting when trying to run the `getAttributes()` method.

@mike-jumper Any pointers on the best place to put the various attribute-related stuff such that it can be easily used across different authentication extensions?"", 'commenter': 'necouchman'}]"

